t: Lament over Defeat in Battle, and Prayer for Help.

For the choir director; according to Shushan Eduth. A Mikhtam of David, to teach; when he struggled with Aram-naharaim and with Aram-zobah, and Joab returned, and smote twelve thousand of Edom in the Valley of Salt.
O*pn God, You have rejected us. You have broken us; You*ln have been angry; O, restore us.
You*ln have made the land quake, You have split it open; Heal*ln its breaches, for it totters.
You*ln have made Your people experience hardship; You*ln have given us wine to drink that makes us stagger.
You*ln have given a banner to those who fear You, That*ln it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.
That*ln Your beloved may be delivered, Save*ln with Your right hand, and answer us!
God*ln has spoken in His holiness: “I*ln will exult, I will portion out Shechem and measure out the valley of Succoth.
Gilead*ln is Mine, and Manasseh is Mine; Ephraim*ln also is the helmet of My head; Judah*ln is My scepter.
Moab*ln is My washbowl; Over*ln Edom I shall throw My shoe; Shout*ln loud, O Philistia, because of Me!”
Who*ln will bring me into the besieged city? Who*ln will lead me to Edom?
Have*ln not You Yourself, O God, rejected us? And*ln will You not go forth with our armies, O God?
O*ln give us help against the adversary, For*ln deliverance by man is in vain.
Through*ln God we shall do valiantly, And*ln it is He who will tread down our adversaries.
